mods.abstract: As listed on insert: Kentucky Colonels at party, Ann Arbor, Michigan (?), 1964 (?) recorded by Mary David. Possibly a listening party of Tut Taylor's Dobro Country recorded by Mary Davis with party goers heard in the background. Listed on container as Kentucky Colonels at party (?). Kentucky Colonels "Rupert Rupenruper and Sons"(SIC) acts, from the Golden Vanity, Ann Arbor, Michigan, 1964. Kentucky Colonels Personnel announced as as Billy Ray (banjo); Clarence White (guitar); Roland White (mandolin); Roger Bush (bass). Audio restricted. Contact for access.
